# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

Successfully configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js application.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files:

1. **src/app/layout.tsx**
   - Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next"`
   - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component inside the `<body>` tag, after the `{children}` element
   - This follows the recommended pattern for Next.js 13.5+ with App Router

2. **package-lock.json**
   - Updated after running `npm install` to ensure dependency consistency
   - The @vercel/speed-insights@1.3.1 package was already present in package.json

## Implementation Details

- **Next.js Version**: 16.1.6 (supports App Router)
- **Package Version**: @vercel/speed-insights@1.3.1 (already installed)
- **Approach**: App Router implementation using SpeedInsights from '@vercel/speed-insights/next'
- **Placement**: Component placed after {children} in the root layout's body tag

## Verification Steps Completed

✅ **Build Test**: Successfully built the project with `npm run build`
   - No compilation errors
   - All routes generated successfully
   - TypeScript type checking passed

✅ **Linter**: Passed eslint with no errors

✅ **Tests**: Ran test suite (one pre-existing failure unrelated to this change)
   - 5 of 6 tests passing
   - The failing test relates to metadata formatting in a different file

✅ **Dependencies**: Updated package-lock.json with npm install

## Notes

- The SpeedInsights component is a self-contained component that automatically tracks Web Vitals and sends data to Vercel when deployed
- No additional configuration is required - it works out of the box
- The component only becomes active when deployed on Vercel (no effect in local development)
- Implementation follows Vercel's official documentation for Next.js App Router
